    <!-- PAGE 2: THE CBAM REALITY -->
    <div class="page" style="background: #fff5f5;">
        <div class="section-tag" style="background-color: rgba(153, 27, 27, 0.1); color: #991b1b;">The Problem</div>
        <div class="grid-2" style="height: 100%; align-items: center;">
            <div>
                <h2 style="color: #991b1b;">CBAM Reality</h2>
                <h3 style="color: #b91c1c; font-size: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px;">CBAM is not just a
                    reporting problem. It is a data, process, and accountability problem.</h3>
                <p><strong>What stakeholders are struggling with today:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Fragmented data across Excel, ERP, emails, invoices, meters, and PDFs</li>
                    <li>No monthly emissions discipline → panic at quarter/year-end</li>
                    <li>Zero audit trail → high rejection and verification risk</li>
                    <li>Confusion around precursors, attribution, and system boundaries</li>
                    <li>Manual CBAM templates that break when scale increases</li>
                    <li>Consultants spending time compiling data instead of advising</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="quote-box">
                <i class="ri-double-quotes-l"></i>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">"CBAM today feels like tax compliance in 1998. EnCBAM modernizes it."</p>
                <div style="margin-top: 40px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 20px;">
                    <div
                        style="width: 60px; height: 60px; background: #991b1b; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; color: white;">
                        <i class="ri-error-warning-line" style="font-size: 30px; position: static; opacity: 1;"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24px; color: #7f1d1d;">Current State</div>
                        <div style="font-size: 18px; color: #991b1b;">High Risk, High Friction</div>
